User: 'if we have companies doing orders to USA for AI DC, they should
be mentioned like Aeroflex, DEE Dev. no static data. all should be automatic.'

This patch surfaces Indian export-supplier midcaps as L4 transmission winners
in BOTH the India view AND (cross-region) the corresponding GLOBAL theme card.

NEW: export_proxy: boolean field on LayerTicker
NEW: export_destination: string (e.g. 'US AI DC + global oil & gas')

INDIA_ROSTER L4 EXPANSION (export proxies):
  AEROFLEX.NS    Stainless steel flexible hoses → US data-center cooling, oil/gas
  DEE.NS         Process piping → US/EU LNG + DC mechanical
  WELCORP.NS     Line pipes → US + Middle East oil & gas
  JINDALSAW.NS   Large-diameter pipes → global oil/gas/water
  ASTRAL.NS      Pipe fittings → GCC + EU plumbing
  HONAUT.NS      Honeywell India embedded automation → global Honeywell parent
  CENTUM.NS      Avionics + defence + DC embedded → global aero/defence/DC
  SONACOMS.NS    EV gears / traction motors → global EV OEMs
  WALCHANNAG.NS  Nuclear vessels + defence heavy eng → global nuclear/defence
  AIAENG.NS      High-chrome grinding media → global mining/cement
  GRINDWELL.NS   Abrasives → Saint-Gobain global

NODE_RULES_IN MANDATORY L4 INJECTS UPDATED:
  COMPUTE_INFRA   → AEROFLEX + HONAUT + CENTUM (DC mechanical + electronics)
  COOLING_INFRA   → AEROFLEX + HONAUT (DC cooling exports)
  OIL_GAS_INFRA   → WELCORP + JINDALSAW + DEE + AEROFLEX
  NUCLEAR_INFRA   → WALCHANNAG (nuclear heavy engineering exports)
  DEFENSE_INFRA   → CENTUM + WALCHANNAG (avionics + heavy eng)

CROSS-REGION SURFACING:
  When deriveLayeredBeneficiaries runs region='GLOBAL', appends India
  export-proxy entries to L4 (up to per_layer_limit/2 reserved slots).
  Net effect: US AI DC card now also shows AEROFLEX/DEE/HONAUT alongside
  US-listed names; global oil-gas card shows WELCORP/JINDALSAW/DEE
  alongside LIN/AI.PA/HON.

CONVEXITY BOOST: +12 for export_proxy=true (export proxies are typically
small/midcap with strong orderbook torque on global capex cycles).

The auto-discovery accumulator continues to discover new export-proxy
candidates organically when news mentions them alongside relevant
SystemNode-classified content.

Type-check clean.
